        public static InternalSolidFireElement create(String mvip,
                              String username,
                              String password)
        Create a new instance of InternalSolidFireElement with a connection to the given target with the appropriate username and password. Hostname verification is defaulted to false.
        Parameters:
        mvip - the management virtual IP (MVIP)
        username - admin username
        password - admin password
        Returns:
        an instance of the Internal SolidFire Element

      • create

        public static InternalSolidFireElement create(String target,
                              String username,
                              String password,
                              boolean verifySSL)
        Create a new instance of InternalSolidFireElement with a connection to the given target with the appropriate username and password. The instance will be initialized at the maximum supported version of the API.
        Parameters:
        target - the management virtual IP (or hostname)
        username - admin username
        password - admin password
        verifySSL - if set to true, the target will be checked against the list of valid SSL hosts, including verification of the validity of the Cert recorded for a given target, otherwise these validity checks are ignored, which is useful when the target is an IP address.
        Returns:
        an instance of the Internal SolidFire Element
        See Also:
        getMaxApiVersion()
